LOGIN TO SALESFORCE OR CREATE A NEW DEV ORG
IN SETUP  Quick Find Box SEARCH DevHub and enable dev org
Then go to profile search salesforceDLX and check the box then save.
In App launcher search namespace registries then link namespace 
It takes 2-5 minutes to link the namespace to the org prefix you want.
Then go to vs code and create project 
Go to vs code and then  sfdx project json fill namespace with your namespace registries

Then authorize a dev org where dev hub is enabled.
sfdx force:org:create -s -f config/project-scratch-def.json -a text@gmail.com-org   --durationdays 30    
It generates the username of scratch org
sfdx force:user:password:generate --targetusername test-ll2u1eou9lxe@example.com  (scrach org id)
sfdx force:user:display --targetusername test-ll2u1eou9lxe@example.com
It fetches the details of your org and save it  to Notepad 
In description, you have a login URL copy the login URL and paste into Chrome 
And login through username and password
